ABTMSE
  • Reference
  • Articles

An S4 class object that contains all observation model

Name
The name of the observation model object
Ccv
a 2 item vector specifying the range in catch observation error as lognormal sd (upper lower)
Cbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of catch bias as a lognormal sd
nCAAobs
a 2 item vector specifying the range in the number of annual catch-at-age observations
nCALobs
a 2 item vector specifying the range in the number of annual catch-at-length observations
Lcv
the variance in lengths by age class log normal sd (currently unused)
Ibeta
a 2 item vector representing the range of hyperstability in indices (currently unused)
Icv
a 2 item vector representing bounds the degree of uncertainty (noise) in relative abundance indices as a lognormal sd (upper lower)(currently unused)
Mbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in natural mortality rate as a lognormal sd
Kbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in growth rate K as a lognormal sd
t0bcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in growth parameter t0 as a normal cv
Linfbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in maximum size Linf as a lognormal sd
LFCbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in the length at first capture as a lognormal sd
LFSbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in the length at full selection as a lognormal sd
FMSYbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated FMSY as a lognormal sd
FMSY_Mbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated FMSY / natural mortality rate as a lognormal sd
BMSY_B0bcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated ratio of BMSY relative to unfished as a lognormal sd
ageMbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated FMSY / natural mortality rate as a lognormal sd
Dbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated depletion (current SSB relative to unfished) as a lognormal sd
Dcv
a 2 item vector specifying the range in interannual variability in depletion (current SSB relative to unfished) lognormal sd
Btbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated current biomass as a lognormal sd
Btcv
a 2 item vector specifying the range in interannual variability in current biomass as a lognormal sd
Ftbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated current exploitation rate as a lognormal sd
Ftcv
a 2 item vector specifying the range in interannual variability in current exploitation rate as a lognormal sd
hbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated steepness as a lognormal sd
Recbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated recent recruitment strength rate as a lognormal sd
IMSYbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated target relative abundance index as a lognormal sd
MSYbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated MSY (a target catch rate) as a lognormal sd
BMSYbcv
a 2 item vector specifying the maximum extend of bias in simulated BMSY (a target biomass level) as a lognormal sd
MPind
a data frame containing the indices that may be used by MPs in closed loop simulation [year, index number, index name, index, CV, stock, type (1: vulnerable biomass, 2: ssb), source, applies to model areas]
MPind_stats
a list containing the statistical properties of model fits (currently unused)
